  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        A matrix <m>A</m> is a <em>nilpotent</em> matrix if <m>A^m=0</m>,
        i.e., <m>A^m</m> is the zero matrix,
        for some positive integer <m>m</m>.
        Explain why the matrices
        <me>
          A = \left[ \begin{array}{cc} 0 \amp  a \\ 0 \amp  0 \end{array}  \right] \, , \, B = \left[ \begin{array}{ccc} 0 \amp  a \amp  b \\ 0 \amp  0\amp  c\\ 0\amp 0\amp 0 \end{array}  \right]
        </me>
        are nilpotent matrices.
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>A^2=0</m> and <m>B^3=0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Suppose <m>A</m> is an <m>n\times n</m> matrix for which <m>A^2=0</m>.
        Show that there is a matrix <m>B</m> for which
        <m>(I_n+A)B=I_n</m> where <m>I_n</m> is the identity matrix of size <m>n</m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>
        Let <m>A</m>, <m>B</m>, and <m>C</m> be
        <m>m \times n</m> matrices and let <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> be scalars.
        Verify <xref ref="thm_matrix_sum_properties"></xref>.
        That is, show that
      </p>
    </introduction>
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p>
              <m>A+B = B+A</m>
            </p>
          </statement>
          <answer>
            <p>
              <m>[a_{ij} + b_{ij}] = [b_{ij} + a_{ij}]</m>
            </p>
          </answer>
        </task>
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p>
              <m>(A+B) + C = A + (B+C)</m>
            </p>
          </statement>
        </task>
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p>
              The <m>m \times n</m> matrix <m>0</m> whose entries are all 0 has the 
              property that <m>A + 0 = A</m>.
            </p>
          </statement>
          <answer>
            <p>
              <m>[a_{ij} + 0] = [a_{ij}]</m>
            </p>
          </answer>
        </task>
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p>
              The scalar multiple <m>(-1)A</m> of the matrix <m>A</m> has the property 
              that <m>(-1)A + A = 0</m>.
            </p>
          </statement>
        </task>
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p>
              <m>(a+b) A = aA + bA</m>
            </p>
          </statement>
          <answer>
            <p>
              <m>[(a+b)a_{ij}] = [aa_{ij}] + [ba_{ij}]</m>
            </p>
          </answer>
        </task>
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p>
              <m>a(A+B) = aA + aB</m>
            </p>
          </statement>
        </task>
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p>
              <m>(ab) A = a(bA)</m>
            </p>
          </statement>
          <answer>
            <p>
              <m>[(ab)a_{ij}] = a[ba_{ij}]</m>
            </p>
          </answer>
        </task>
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p>
              <m>1A=A</m>.
            </p>
          </statement>
        </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
